<div><div><h2>--</h2></div><div>mumbai: vodafone idea’s independent director uday khanna resigned less than a month into his job  citing “avoidance of any semblance of conflict of interest with his other board positions”.the resignation is effective september 28  the telecom operator said.khanna’s resignation comes within a month of vodafone india and idea cellular merging their operations to create the largest telecom company in india. the two completed the transaction on august 31.according to reports  the former managing director and chief executive of lafarge india serves on the boards of six other companies: murugappa group  bata india  castrol india  pfizer  kotak mahindra bank and pidilite industries.</div></div>